Note:
Rust Translation Round-Trip Probe

End-to-end proof that the Rust translation pipeline is REAL, not a skeleton:

    Rust source
      -> rust_lexer    (streaming tokenizer: keywords as distinct tokens,
                        identifiers, lifetimes, numeric/char/string literals,
                        the full operator/punctuation set incl :: -> => ..= << >>)
      -> rust_parser   (recursive-descent AST: mod, use, a generic struct + impl
                        with methods, an enum with data variants, a trait + impl,
                        a generic fn with where clause, match, if-let, a closure,
                        the ? operator, a for loop)
      -> rust_semantic (real scope/name resolution; validation only)
      -> rust_to_hir   (lower to the canonical hir.runa create_hir_node IR)
      -> hir_to_rust   (emit HIR back to valid Rust text)
      -> re-lex / re-parse / re-to_hir of the emitted text
      -> structural HIR equality on the key constructs

The Rust HIR node model is hir.runa's canonical typed-node model shared by
rust_to_hir (producer) and hir_to_rust (consumer): every node is a 104-byte
HIRNode with node_type at offset 0, the textual payload at offset 40, a children
List at offset 24, and child_count at offset 32. This probe reads HIR fields
through exactly that contract.

It lowers the source to HIR1, asserts HIR1 is a crate module whose declarations
include a process named "area" and a type definition named "Shape", emits HIR1
back to Rust text, re-runs the whole pipeline on the emitted text to HIR2, and
asserts HIR2 is STRUCTURALLY EQUAL to HIR1 on those same key constructs.

Exit code: number of failed assertions (0 == all passed). No exit_with_code.
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/rust/rust_to_hir.runa" as RustFrontend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/rust/hir_to_rust.runa" as RustBackend
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "tests/test_utils.runa" as TestUtils

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Canonical HIRNode decoders (node_type@0, children@24, child_count@32,
Note: value@40) - the exact layout rust_to_hir produces and hir_to_rust reads.
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
The node_type tag lives at offset 0. Centralising the read documents the contract.
@End Reasoning
Process called "hir_kind" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
The textual payload (name/operator/literal) lives at offset 40.
@End Reasoning
Process called "hir_value" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 40
End Process

@Reasoning:
The children List handle lives at offset 24; the count at offset 32. The list is
the same List the producer built via add_hir_node, so List.size/get_at iterate it.
@End Reasoning
Process called "hir_children" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 24
End Process

Process called "hir_child_count" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 32
End Process

@Reasoning:
Positional child access over the children list.
@End Reasoning
Process called "hir_child" takes node as Integer, index as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children be proc hir_children with node
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc get_at from List with children, index
End Process

@Reasoning:
Finds the first child of a node whose node_type tag matches the requested kind AND
whose value (name) string-equals the requested name. Returns 0 if none. This is the
structural locator the assertions use to find a specific function/type by name.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_child_named" takes parent as Integer, kind as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    If parent is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc hir_child_count with parent
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let child be proc hir_child with parent, i
        Let ck be proc hir_kind with child
        If ck is equal to kind:
            Let cv be proc hir_value with child
            Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with cv, name
            If matches is equal to 1:
                Return child
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Pipeline helper
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Each round runs the identical source -> HIR pipeline (parse, validate, lower) via
the public single-arg facade, so any structural divergence is attributable to the
emitter, not to a difference in how the inputs were driven.
@End Reasoning
Process called "source_to_hir" takes source as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc rust_to_hir_from_source from RustFrontend with source
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Probe entry point
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be proc create_test_results from TestUtils
    proc begin_suite from TestUtils with results, "Rust translation round-trip"

    Note:
    Representative program exercising the constructs the task requires: a use
    import, a generic struct, an enum with data variants, a trait, an impl with
    methods (self receiver, generics, where clause, match, if-let, a closure, the
    ? operator, a for loop), and a free generic function.
    :End Note
    Let source be "use std::collections::HashMap;\nstruct Point<T> {\nx: T,\ny: T,\n}\nenum Shape {\nCircle(f64),\nRect { w: f64, h: f64 },\nNothing,\n}\ntrait Area {\nfn area(&self) -> f64;\n}\nimpl Area for Shape {\nfn area(&self) -> f64 {\nlet result = match self {\nShape::Circle(r) => r * r,\nShape::Rect { w, h } => w * h,\nShape::Nothing => 0.0,\n};\nreturn result;\n}\n}\nimpl Shape {\nfn classify<T>(&self, items: Vec<T>) -> i64 where T: Clone {\nlet mut total = 0;\nfor item in items {\ntotal = total + 1;\n}\nif let Shape::Nothing = self {\ntotal = total - 1;\n}\nlet f = |z: i64| z + total;\nlet maybe = compute()?;\nreturn f(total);\n}\n}\nfn area(s: Shape) -> f64 {\nreturn s.area();\n}\n"

    Note: --- Stage 0-2: source -> HIR1 (parse, validate, lower) ---
    Let hir1 be proc rust_to_hir_from_source from RustFrontend with source
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "frontend produced HIR module", hir1

    Note: HIR root is the crate module; it must have declarations.
    Let root_kids be proc hir_child_count with hir1
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "crate has declarations", root_kids, 0

    Note: --- free function `area` present at the crate root (located by name) ---
    Let area_node be proc find_named_any with hir1, "area"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "function 'area' lowered", area_node

    Note: --- generic struct `Point` present ---
    Let point_node be proc find_named_any with hir1, "Point"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "struct 'Point' lowered", point_node
    Let point_fields be proc hir_child_count with point_node
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "Point has 2 fields", point_fields, 2

    Note: --- enum `Shape` present with variants ---
    Let shape_node be proc find_named_any with hir1, "Shape"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "enum 'Shape' lowered", shape_node
    Let shape_variants be proc hir_child_count with shape_node
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "Shape has 3 variants", shape_variants, 3

    Note: --- method `area` (inside impl) and `classify` present somewhere ---
    Let classify_node be proc find_named_any with hir1, "classify"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "method 'classify' lowered", classify_node

    Note: --- Stage 3: HIR1 -> Rust text ---
    Let emitted be proc hir_to_rust from RustBackend with hir1
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "backend produced Rust text", emitted
    Let emitted_len be proc string_length from StringCore with emitted
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "emitted Rust is non-empty", emitted_len, 0

    Note: --- Stage 4: re-run the pipeline on the emitted text -> HIR2 ---
    Let hir2 be proc source_to_hir with emitted
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "re-parse of emitted Rust produced HIR", hir2
    Let root2_kids be proc hir_child_count with hir2
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "round-trip crate has declarations", root2_kids, 0

    Note: --- Stage 5: structural equality on the key constructs ---
    Let area2 be proc find_named_any with hir2, "area"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves function 'area'", area2
    Let area_same be proc same_kind with area_node, area2
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves 'area' node kind", area_same, 1

    Let point2 be proc find_named_any with hir2, "Point"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves struct 'Point'", point2
    Let point_same be proc same_kind with point_node, point2
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves 'Point' node kind", point_same, 1

    Let shape2 be proc find_named_any with hir2, "Shape"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves enum 'Shape'", shape2
    Let shape2_variants be proc hir_child_count with shape2
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves Shape variants", shape2_variants, 3

    Let classify2 be proc find_named_any with hir2, "classify"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves method 'classify'", classify2

    proc print_summary from TestUtils with results
    Let failed be proc get_failed from TestUtils with results
    proc destroy_test_results from TestUtils with results

    Return failed
End Process

@Reasoning:
Recursively searches the whole HIR tree for the first node (of any kind) whose
value string-equals the requested name. This is the robust locator for a named
declaration regardless of whether it sits at the crate root or inside an impl/trait
module grouping.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_named_any" takes parent as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    If parent is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pv be proc hir_value with parent
    If pv is not equal to 0:
        Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with pv, name
        If matches is equal to 1:
            Return parent
        End If
    End If
    Let count be proc hir_child_count with parent
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let child be proc hir_child with parent, i
        Let found be proc find_named_any with child, name
        If found is not equal to 0:
            Note: do not return the crate root itself when it merely contains the
            Note: name deeper; the recursion already returns the deepest match.
            Return found
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Two HIR nodes are structurally equal on a construct when both carry the same
node_type tag - a whitespace-insensitive fidelity check that survives the emitter's
re-indentation.
@End Reasoning
Process called "same_kind" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ka be proc hir_kind with a
    Let kb be proc hir_kind with b
    If ka is equal to kb:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process
